{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"812a648c-4477-447c-a9ea-94be254adcc0","content":"The workspace is empty, so this is a general guidance question. Based on the repository conventions (the skill-validator framework uses `evaluation.yml`), here's what you need:\n\n## Evaluation Format\n\nEvaluations are defined in an **`evaluation.yml`** file in your skill plugin directory. Each entry is a question with acceptance criteria that the skill-validator runs against your MCP server.\n\n### Structure\n\n```yaml\n- question: \"What products are available under $50?\"\n  criteria:\n    - The response must include product names and prices\n    - All listed products must have a price below 50\n    - The model must call the search_products tool\n\n- question: \"Compare the specs of ProductA and ProductB\"\n  criteria:\n    - The response must reference both products by name\n    - Key specifications must be compared side by side\n    - The model must call get_product_details at least twice\n```\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n| Quality | Example |\n|---|---|\n| **Tests tool selection** | \"Find all wireless headphones\" → expects `search_products` |\n| **Tests multi-tool chaining** | \"Is ProductA cheaper than ProductB?\" → requires two lookups + comparison |\n| **Tests filtering/parameters** | \"Show me electronics under $100 sorted by rating\" → tests correct parameter usage |\n| **Tests edge cases** | \"Find product XYZ-000\" → verifies graceful handling of no results |\n| **Has verifiable criteria** | Criteria reference concrete facts from your catalog data |\n\n### Tips\n- **Ground in real data** — criteria should be checkable against your catalog so results are deterministic.\n- **Vary complexity** — mix single-tool, multi-tool, and reasoning-heavy questions.\n- **Test failure modes** — include queries with no matches or ambiguous input.\n- **Be specific in criteria** — \"must call `search_products` with category='electronics'\" is better than \"should search correctly.\"","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc104330-8f90-4fef-9734-2e0edc150f62","outputTokens":444,"requestId":"D024:2F2B7:14C5E4E:1740F74:6A0672C0"},"id":"58d56ec2-afa1-409b-b952-f987c22c45e4","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:11:41.145Z","parentId":"45ceb3af-6f52-4665-a051-e493d06c211f"}
